καρδία κ. καὶ ἀγαθή, Lk 8:15; παραθήκη, II Ti 1:14; μέτρον, Lk 6:38; βαθμός, I Ti 3:13; θεμέλιος, I Ti 6:19; τὸ κ., I Th 5:21; μαργαρίται, Mt 13:45; οἶνος, Jo 2:10; ποιμήν, Jo 10:11, 14; διάκονος, I Ti 4:6; οἰκονόμος, I Pe 4:10; στρατιώτης, II Ti 2:3; στρατεία, I Ti 1:18; ἀγών, I Ti 6:12, II Ti 4:7; ὁμολογία, I Ti 6:12, 13; ἔργον, Mt 26:10, Mk 14:6, Jo 10:33, I Ti 3:1; pl., Jo 10:32; καλόν, c. inf. et dat., Mt 18:8, 9 I Co 7:1, 26 9:15; id. c. acc. et inf., Mt 17:4, Mk 9:5, 43, 45, 47, Lk 9:33, He 13:9; seq. εἰ, Mt 26:24, Mk 9:42 14:21; ἐάν, I Co 7:8. Ethically, good, in the sense of right, fair, noble, honourable: Ga 4:18, He 5:14; ἔργα, Mt 5:16, I Ti 5:10, 25 6:18, Tit 2:7, 14 3:8, 14 (Field, Notes, 223f.), He 10:24, I Pe 2:12; ἀναστροφή, Ja 3:13, I Pe 2:12; συνείδησις, He 13:18; seq. ἐνώπιον, Ro 12:17, II Co 8:21, I Ti 2:3; το] κ. ποιεῖν (κατεργάζεσθαι), Ro 7:18, 21 II Co 13:7, Ga 6:9, Ja 4:17; καλόν ἐστιν, c. inf., Mt 15:26 (T, ἔξεστιν), Mk 7:27, Ro 14:21, Ga 4:18; μαρτυρία, I Ti 3:7; ὄνομα, Ja 2:7; καύχημα, I Co 5:6 (neg.); θεοῦ ῥῆμα, He 6:5. κ. does not occur in Re.†
SYN.: v.s. ἀγαθός.

down, downwards. 
    C. gen. (WM, §47, k; Bl., §42, 2). 
      C. gen. rei, in local sense; 
	down, down from: Mt 8:32, Mk 5:13, Lk 8:33, I Co 11:4; 
	throughout (late usage; Bl, l.c.): κ. ὅλης κ.τ.λ., Lk 4:14  23:5, Ac 9:31  10:37; 
	in a peculiar adjectival phrase: ἡ κ. βάθους, deep or extreme poverty, II Co 8:2. 
      C. gen. pers., usually in hostile sense; 
	against (in cl. only after verbs of speaking, witnessing, etc.): opp. to ὑπέρ, Mk 9:40; μετά, Mt 12:30; after ἐπιθυμεῖν, Ga 5:17; λαλεῖν, Ac 6:13; διδάσκειν, Ac 21:28; ψεύδεσθαι, Ja 3:14; after verbs of accusing, etc., Mt 5:23, Lk 23:14, Ro 8:33, al.; verbs of fighting, prevailing, etc., Mt 10:35, Ac 14:2, I Co 4:6, al.; 
	of swearing, by: όμνυμι κ. (BL, §34, 1), He  6:13,16, cf. Mt 26:63. 
    C. acc. (WM, §49d; BL, §42, 2). 
      Of motion or direction; 
	through, throughout: Lk 8:39  9:6 10:4, Ac 8:1,  36 al.; 
	to, towards, over against: Lk 10:32 (Field, Notes, 62), Ac 2:1o 16:7, Ga 2:11, Phl 3:14, al.; 
	in adverbial phrases, at, in, by, of: κατ’ 

 οἶκον, at home, Ac 2:46; κατ’ ἰδίαν (v.s. ἴδιος); καθ’ ἑαυτόν, Ac 28:16, Ro 14:22, Ja 2:17; c. pron. pers., Ac 17:28  18:15, Ro 1:15, Eph 1:15, al. 
      Of time, at, during, about: Ac 8:26  12:1 19:23, Ro 9:9 He 1:10, al. 
      Distributive; 
	of place: κ. τόποὐς, Mt 24:7, al.; κ. πόλιν, Lk 8:1,  4 al.; κ. ἐκκλησίαν, Ac 14:23. 
	of time: κ. ἔτος, Lk 2:41; ἑορτήν, Mt 27:15, al.; 
	of numbers, etc.: καθ’ ἕνα πάντες, I Co 14:31 (on καθ’ εἷς, v.s. εἷς); κ. ἑκατόν, Mk 6:40; κ. μέρος, He 9:5; κ. ὄνομα, Jo 10:3. 
      Of fitness, reference, conformity, etc.; 
	in relation to, concerning: Ro 1:3, 4 7:22 9:3, 5, I Co 12:6  10:18, Phl 1:12; κ. πάντα, Ac 17:22, Col 3:20,  22 He 2:17  4:15; 
	according to, after, like: Mk 7:5, Lk 2:27,  29 Jo 7:24 Ro 8:4  14:15, Eph 2:2, Col 2:8, Ja 2:8, al. 
    In composition, κ. denotes, 
      down, down from (καταβαίνω), etc.), hence, metaph.; 
	victory or rule over (καταδουλόω, -κυριεύω, etc.); 
	"perfective" action (M, Pr., 111ff.). 
      under (κατακαλύπτω), etc.). 
      in succession (καθεξῆς). 
      after, behind (καταλείπω). 
      Hostility, against (καταλαλέω).

    order (Hom., Plat., al.). 
    ornament, adornment, esp. of women (Hom., al.): I Pe 3:3. 
    Later, the world or universe, as an ordered system (Plat., al.): Ac 17:24, Ro 4:13, I Co 3:22, Phl 2:15, He 4:3, al. 
    In late writers only, the world, i.e. the earth (= ἡ οἰκουμένη, cf. Mt 4:8 with Lk 4:5): Mt 4:8, Mk 16:[15], Col 2:20, I Ti 6:7, al.; hence by meton., 
      of the human inhabitants of the world: Mt 5:14  15:38, Mk 14:9, Jo 1:10  4:42 12:47, Ro 3:6, I Co 4:13, II Co 5:19, II Pe 2:5, al.; 
      of worldly affairs or possessions: Mt 16:26, Mk 8:36, Lk 9:25, I Co 7:31, I Jo 2:16, al.; 
      in ethical sense, of the ungodly: Jo 7:7  14:17,  27 I Co 1:21, Ja 1:27, I Jo 4:4, al.; 
      metaph.: ὁ κ. τῆς ἀδικίας, Ja 3:6. 


SYN.: αἰών, q.v. (cf . also Dalman, Words, 162ff.; Tr., Syn., §lix; Westc., additional note on Jo 1:10; DB, iv, 938ff.).

great; 
    of external form, bodily size, measure, extent: λίθος, Mt 2:60; δράκων, Re 12:3; ἰχθῦς, Jo 21:11; πόλις, Re 11:8; μάχαιρα, Re 6:4, al. 
    Of intensity and degree: δύναμις, Ac 4:33; φόβος, Mk 4:41; ἀγάπη, Jo 15:13; ἄνεμος, ib. 6:18; κραυγή, Ac 23:9; φῶς, Mt 4:16; πυρετός, Lk 4:38; θλίψις, Mt 24:21. 
    Of rank; 
      of persons: θεός (MM, xvi), Tit 2:13; Ἄρτεμις, Ac 19:27; compar. (v. infr.), Mt 18:1 (cf. Dalman, Words, 113f.); neut. for masc. (Bl., §32, 1), Mt 12:6; 
      of things: ἁμαρτία, Jo 19:11; μυστήριον, Eph 5:32; = μεγίστη (v. infr., and cf. Field, Notes, 16f.), Mt 22:36; compar. for superl. (M, Pr., 78), I Co 13:13. 


      Compar., μείζων: Mt 11:11  23:17, al.; neut. pl., μείζονα, contr. μείζω, Jo 1:51; double compar., μειζότερος (M, Pr., 236; Bl., §11, 4), III Jo 4; 
      superl, μέγιστος (Deiss., BS, 365), II Pe 1:4.

to be about to be or do; 
    c. inf. (Bl., §62, 4; 68, 2; M, Pr., 114); 
      of intending or being about to do of 

 one's own free will: c. inf. praes., Mt 2:13, Lk 10:1, Ac 3:3  5:35, He 8:5, II Pe 1:12 (Field, Notes, 240), al.; c. inf. aor. (Bl., §58, 3), Ac 12:6, Re 3:16; 
      of compulsion, necessity or certainty: c. inf. praes., Mt 16:27, Lk 9:31, Jo 6:71, Ro 4:24, al.; c. inf. aor., Ro 8:18, Ga 3:23, Re 3:2  12:4. 

    Ptcp., ὁ μέλλων: absol., Ro 8:38, I Co 3:22; τὰ μ., Col 2:17; εἰς τὸ μ. (Field, Notes, 65); c. subst., Mt 3:7  12:32 (ὁ αἰὼν ὁ μ.; LXX for עַד), Ac 24:25, I Ti 4:8, He 2:5, al.

to stay, abide, remain. 
    Intrans.; 
      of place: seq. ἐν, Lk 8:27, al.; παρά, c. dat. pers., Jo 1:40, al; σύν, Lk 1:56; καθ’ ἑαυτόν, Ac 28:16; c. adv., ἐκεῖ, Mt 10:11; ὧδε, Mt 26:38; metaph., I Jo 2:18; of the Holy Spirit, Jo 1:32, 33 14:17; of Christ, Jo 6:56  15:4, al.; ὁ θεός, I Jo 4:15, conversely, of Christians, Jo 6:56  15:4,
 I Jo 4:15, al.; ὁ λόγος τ. θεοῦ, I Jo 2:14; ἡ ἀλήθεια, II Jo 2, al. 
      Of time; 
	of persons: Phl 1:25; seq. εἰς τ. αἰῶνα, Jo 12:34, He 7:24, I Jo 2:17; ὀλίγον, Re 17:10; ἕως ἔρχομαι, Jo 21:22, 23; 
	of things, lasting or enduring: cities, Mt 11:23, He 13:14; λόγος θεοῦ, I Pe 1:23; ἁμαρτία, Jo 9:41. 

      Of condition: c. pred., μόνος, Jo 12:24; ἄγαμος, I Co 7:11; πιστός, II Ti 2:13; ἱερεύς, He 7:3; c. adv., οὕτως, I Co 7:40; ὡς κἀγώ, ib. 8; seq. ἐν, ib. 20, 24. 

    Trans. (Bl., §34, 1; Field, Notes, 132): c. acc. pers., Ac 20:5, 23 (cf. ἀνα-, δια-, ἐν-, ἐπι-, κατα-, παρα-, συν-παρα-, περι-, προσ-, ὑπο-μένω).

used where the negation depends on a condition or hypothesis, expressed or understood, as distinct from οὐ, which denies absolutely. μή is used where one thinks a thing is not, as distinct from an absolute negation. As a general rule, οὐ negatives the indic, μή the other moods, incl, ptcp. [In LXX for אֵין ,אַיִן ,אַל]


    As a neg. adv., not; 
      with ref. to thought or opinion: Jo 3:18, Tit 1:11, II Pe 1:9.  
      In delib. questions, c. subjc. (M, Pr., 185): Mk 12:14, Ro 3:8.  
      In conditional and final sentences, after εἰ, ἐάν, ἄν, ἵνα, ὅπως: Mt 10:14, Mk 6:11 12:19, Lk 9:5, Jo 6:50, Ro 11:25, al.  
      C. inf. (v. M, Pr., 234f., 239, 255), 
        after verbs of saying, etc.: Mt 2:12 5:34, Mk 12:18, Ac 15:38, Ro 2:21, al.;  
        c. artic. inf.: after a prep., Mt 13:5, Mk 4:5, Ac 7:19, I Co 10:6, al.; without a prep., Ro 14:13, II Co 2:1, 13, 1 Th 4:6;  
        in sentences expressing consequence, after ὥστε: Mt 8:28, Mk 3:20, I Co 1:7, II Co 3:7, al.  
      C. ptcp. (v. M, Pr., 231f., 239), in hypothetical references to persons of a certain character or description: Mt 10:28 12:30, Lk 6:49, Jo 3:18, Ro 4:5, I Co 7:38, I Jo 3:10, al.; where the person or thing being definite, the denial is a matter of opinion: Jo 6:64, I Co 1:28 4:7, 18, II Co 5:21, al.; where the ptcp. has a concessive, causal or conditional force, if, though, because not: Mt 18:25, Lk 2:45, Jo 7:49, Ac 9:26, Ro 2:14 5:13, II Co 3:14, Ga 6:9, Ju 5; where the ptcp. has a descriptive force (being such as), not: Ac 9:9, Ro 1:28, I Co 10:33, Ga 4:8, He 12:27, al.  
      μή prohibitive, in indep. sentences, 
        c. subjc. praes., 1 pers. pl.: Ga 5:26 6:9, I Th 5:6, I Jo 3:18;  
        c. imperat. praes., usually where one is bidden to desist from what has already begun (cf. M, Pr., 122ff.): Mt 7:1, Mk 5:36, Lk 6:30, Jo 2:16 5:45, Ac 10:15, Ro 11:18, Ja 2:1, Re 5:5, al.;  
        forbidding that which is still future: c. imperat. aor., 3 pers., Mt 24:18, Mk 13:15, Lk 17:31, al.; c. subjc. aor., 2 pers., Mt 3:9 10:26, Mk 5:7, Lk 6:29, Jo 3:7, Ro 10:6, al.;  
        c. optat., in wishes: II Ti 4:16 (LXX); μὴ γένοιτο (v. M, Pr., 194; Bl., §66, 1), Lk 20:16, Ro 3:3, al.; μή τις, Mk 13:5, al. 

    As a conj., 
      after verbs of fearing, caution, etc., that, lest, perhaps (M, Pr., 192f.): c. subjc. praes., He 12:15; c. subjc. aor., Mt 24:4, Mk 13:5, Lk 21:8, Ac 13:40, Ga 5:15, al.; ὅρα μή (v. M, Pr., 124, 178), elliptically, Re 19:10 22:9; c. indic, fut. (M, Pr., l.c.), Col 2:8.  
      in order that not: c. subjc. aor., Mk 13:36, II Co 8:20 12:6. 

    Interrogative, in hesitant questions (M, Pr., 170), or where a negative answer is expected: Mt 7:9, 10, Mk 2:19, Jo 3:4, Ro 3:3 10:18, 19, I Co 1:13, al.; μή τις, Lk 22:35, al.; seq. οὐ (Ro 10:17, al. in Pl.), expecting an affirm, ans.; οὐ μή, Lk 18:7, Jo 18:11. 

    οὐ μή as emphatic negation (cf. M, Pr., 188, 190ff.; Bl. §64, 5), not at all, by no means: c. indic, fut., Mt 16:22, Jo 6:35, He 10:17, al.; c. subjc. aor., Mt 24:2, Mk 13:2, Lk 6:37, Jo 13:8, I Co 8:13, al.

